{"id":"shavsha","term":"Shavsha","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(“Seraiah,” <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Samuel 8:17\">2 Sam. 8:17</a>; “Shisha,” <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 4:3\">1 Kings 4:3</a>), one of David’s secretaries (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 18:16\">1 Chr. 18:16</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["2 Samuel 8:17","1 Kings 4:3","1 Chronicles 18:16"]}